# Focus Mode C (AF-C)

| Option       | Description                                                                 | Sample Image                  |
|--------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------|
| SINGLE POINT | Focus tracks subject at selected focus point. Use for subjects moving toward or away from camera. | !Single Point |
| ZONE         | Camera tracks focus in selected focus zone. Use for subjects that are moving fairly predictably. | !Zone         |
| TRACKING     | Focus tracks subjects moving through wide area of frame.                    | !Tracking     |
| ALL          | Rotate the rear command dial in the focus-point selection display (ðŸ“– 87, 88) to cycle through AF modes in the following order: SINGLE POINT, ZONE, and TRACKING. |                               |
